t may hinder development. In addition, they show how the domestic policies required to implement laws may undermine India’s treaty obligations at the World Trade Organization or under the Agreement on Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights. The contributors ultimately ask whether development can be achieved by making it a legal right and whether India’s right to develop is truly at odds with its international commitments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic developmentxMoral and ethical aspectszIndia. 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspectszIndia. 0aEconomic developmentzIndia. 0aHuman rightszIndia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Developing & Emerging Countries.2bisacsh1 aDeshpande, Ashwini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarding, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirsch, Moshe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirsch, Moshe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKandlikar, Milind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKotwal, Ashok, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKotwal, Ashok, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKulkarni, Ashwini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalhotra, Nisha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurugkar, Milind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, Pitman B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamaswami, Bharat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamaswami, Bharat, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWadhwa, Wllima, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/